def plotAttribute(featureName):
    oneSTD = data[featureName].std()
    twoSTD = oneSTD * 2
    threeSTD = oneSTD * 3
    meanValue = data[featureName].mean()

    
    print("Attribue:", featureName.upper())
    print("Summary:")
    instances = data.shape[0]
    outsideTwo = ((data[featureName] < (meanValue - twoSTD)).sum() + (data[featureName] > (meanValue + twoSTD)).sum())
    outsideThree = ((data[featureName] < (meanValue - threeSTD)).sum() + (data[featureName] > (meanValue + threeSTD)).sum())
    
    print("N outside of two STD:\t", outsideTwo, "\t(", round((outsideTwo/instances) *100, 2),"%)")
    print("N outside of three STD:\t", outsideThree, "\t(", round((outsideThree/instances) * 100, 2),"%)")
    

    plt.axvline(x=(meanValue - oneSTD), label='One STD', c="g")
    plt.axvline(x=(meanValue + oneSTD), c="g")
    
    plt.axvline(x=(meanValue - twoSTD), label='Two STD', c="y")
    plt.axvline(x=(meanValue + twoSTD), c="y")
    
    plt.axvline(x=(meanValue - threeSTD), label='Three STD', c="r")
    plt.axvline(x=(meanValue + threeSTD), c="r")
    
    data[featureName].hist(figsize=(7,7))
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()
    
    
def runMLAlgorithms():
    # Folds and seed
    num_folds = 10
    seed = 1
    kfold = KFold(n_splits=num_folds, random_state=seed)
    
    # LR
    try:
        model = LogisticRegression()
        results = cross_val_score(model, attributes, classLabels, cv=kfold)
        y_pred = cross_val_predict(model, attributes, classLabels, cv=kfold)
        conf_mat = confusion_matrix(classLabels, y_pred)
        tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(classLabels, y_pred).ravel()
        sensitivity = (tp / (tp + fn))*100
        specificity = (tn / (tn + fp))*100
        print("{:<30}".format("Logistic regression"), end="")
        print("{:<10}".format(str(round(results.mean()*100.0,2))+"%"),end="")
        print("{:<10}".format(str(round(sensitivity,2))+"%"),end="")
        print("{:<10}".format(str(round(specificity,2))+"%"),end="")
        print()
    except:
        model = LogisticRegression(solver='liblinear')
        results = cross_val_score(model, attributes, classLabels, cv=kfold)
        y_pred = cross_val_predict(model, attributes, classLabels, cv=kfold)
        conf_mat = confusion_matrix(classLabels, y_pred)
        tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(classLabels, y_pred).ravel()
        sensitivity = (tp / (tp + fn))*100
        specificity = (tn / (tn + fp))*100
        print("{:<30}".format("Logistic regression"), end="")
        print("{:<10}".format(str(round(results.mean()*100.0,2))+"%"),end="")
        print("{:<10}".format(str(round(sensitivity,2))+"%"),end="")
        print("{:<10}".format(str(round(specificity,2))+"%"),end="")
        print()
    
    #SVM
    model = svm.SVC(kernel='linear')
    results = cross_val_score(model, attributes, classLabels, cv=kfold)
    y_pred = cross_val_predict(model, attributes, classLabels, cv=kfold)
    conf_mat = confusion_matrix(classLabels, y_pred)
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(classLabels, y_pred).ravel()
    sensitivity = (tp / (tp + fn))*100
    specificity = (tn / (tn + fp))*100
    print("{:<30}".format("SVM"), end="")
    print("{:<10}".format(str(round(results.mean()*100.0,2))+"%"),end="")
    print("{:<10}".format(str(round(sensitivity,2))+"%"),end="")
    print("{:<10}".format(str(round(specificity,2))+"%"),end="")
    print()
    
    model = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=3)
    results = cross_val_score(model, attributes, classLabels, cv=kfold)
    y_pred = cross_val_predict(model, attributes, classLabels, cv=kfold)
    conf_mat = confusion_matrix(classLabels, y_pred)
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(classLabels, y_pred).ravel()
    sensitivity = (tp / (tp + fn))*100
    specificity = (tn / (tn + fp))*100
    print("{:<30}".format("KNN"), end="")
    print("{:<10}".format(str(round(results.mean()*100.0,2))+"%"),end="")
    print("{:<10}".format(str(round(sensitivity,2))+"%"),end="")
    print("{:<10}".format(str(round(specificity,2))+"%"),end="")
    print()
    
    model = DecisionTreeClassifier()
    results = cross_val_score(model, attributes, classLabels, cv=kfold)
    y_pred = cross_val_predict(model, attributes, classLabels, cv=kfold)
    conf_mat = confusion_matrix(classLabels, y_pred)
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(classLabels, y_pred).ravel()
    sensitivity = (tp / (tp + fn))*100
    specificity = (tn / (tn + fp))*100
    print("{:<30}".format("Decision Tree"), end="")
    print("{:<10}".format(str(round(results.mean()*100.0,2))+"%"),end="")
    print("{:<10}".format(str(round(sensitivity,2))+"%"),end="")
    print("{:<10}".format(str(round(specificity,2))+"%"),end="")
    print()
    
    model = GaussianNB()
    results = cross_val_score(model, attributes, classLabels, cv=kfold)
    y_pred = cross_val_predict(model, attributes, classLabels, cv=kfold)
    conf_mat = confusion_matrix(classLabels, y_pred)
    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(classLabels, y_pred).ravel()
    sensitivity = (tp / (tp + fn))*100
    specificity = (tn / (tn + fp))*100
    print("{:<30}".format("Naive Bayes"), end="")
    print("{:<10}".format(str(round(results.mean()*100.0,2))+"%"),end="")
    print("{:<10}".format(str(round(sensitivity,2))+"%"),end="")
    print("{:<10}".format(str(round(specificity,2))+"%"),end="")
    print()
    
    
def deepLearning():
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(Dense(1000, input_dim=(len(finalData.columns.values.tolist())-1), activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dense(8000, activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dense(1, activation='sigmoid'))
    model.compile(loss='binary_crossentropy', optimizer='adam',metrics=['acc'])

    # Fit the model using GPU - Forced
    results = model.fit(attributes, classLabels, validation_split=0.33, epochs=400, verbose=0)
    plt.plot(results.history["acc"])
    plt.plot(results.history["val_acc"])
    plt.show()

# creating instance of labelencoder
labelencoder = LabelEncoder()

print("\n\nColumn Names & formatting:\n")



for col in data.columns.values.tolist():
    if data[col].dtype == "object" or data[col].dtype == "bool":
        print("{:<20}".format(col), ":", "{:<20}".format(str(data[col].dtype)) , "Formatting to LabelEncoding")
        data[col] = labelencoder.fit_transform(data[col])
    else:
        print("{:<30}".format(col), ":", "{:<20}".format(str(data[col].dtype)) , "No formatting required.")

Removing Missing Data¶

In [6]:
option = input("Do you want to delete missing values?: (y/n) ")

if option == "y":
    missingValue = int(input("What is the missing/null value to delete:"))
    print("Number of instances before: ", len(data))
    data = data.mask(data == missingValue, np.NaN)
    data.dropna(inplace=True)
    print("Number of instances after : ", len(data))
    print()
    print(data.describe())
    
    print()
    print("Class Breakdown")
    class_counts = data.groupby(data.columns.values.tolist()[-1]).size()
    print(class_counts)

# Histograms including 1-3 STD's
for col in data.columns.values.tolist():
    print()
    print("*"*30)
    print("Attribute: ", col)
    print("*"*30)
    print(data[col].describe())
    print()
    plotAttribute(col)

# pearson correlation to class value
PCnames = []
PCvalues = []

print()
for col in data.columns.values.tolist()[:-1]:
    print("{:<30}".format(col), round(data[col].corr(data[data.columns.values.tolist()[-1]]),2))
    PCnames.append(col)
    PCvalues.append(abs(round(data[col].corr(data[data.columns.values.tolist()[-1]]),2)))
    

# sort the two lists based on PC values
PCvalues, PCnames  = zip(*sorted(zip(PCvalues, PCnames)))    
    
plt.plot(PCvalues)
plt.show()

for i,name in enumerate(PCnames):
    print("{:<30}".format(name), round(PCvalues[i],2))

# Regression analysis
REGnames = []
REGvalues = []

attributes = data.values[:,0:(len(data.columns.values.tolist())-1)]
classLabels = data.values[:,(len(data.columns.values.tolist())-1)].astype('int')

test = feature_selection.SelectKBest(score_func=feature_selection.f_regression, k=4)
fit = test.fit(attributes, classLabels)

allReg = []

print()
# have to manually display as no function to do so available
for index, result in enumerate(fit.scores_):
    print("{0:30}".format(data.columns.values.tolist()[index]),"{0:20}".format(round(result,2)))
    REGnames.append(data.columns.values.tolist()[index])
    REGvalues.append(abs(round(result,2)))

# sort the two lists based on PC values
REGvalues, REGnames  = zip(*sorted(zip(REGvalues, REGnames)))    
    
plt.plot(REGvalues)
plt.show()

for i,name in enumerate(REGnames):
    print("{:<30}".format(name), round(REGvalues[i],2))

Drop columns¶

In [11]:
print("Dropping Columns:")
print("1) Manually Drop Columns")
print("2) Drop columns by minimum Pearsons correlation")
print("3) Drop columns by multiple regression analysis")
print("4) No Columns to drop")
option = int(input("Please select option: "))

finalData = data.copy()


if option == 1:
    ans = -1

    while ans != 0:
        for i, col in enumerate(finalData.columns.values.tolist()[:-1]):
            print(i+1, ") ", col)

        ans = int(input("Please enter column to delete (0 to exit)"))
        if ans > 0:
            print("Dropping column : ", finalData.columns.values.tolist()[ans-1])
            del finalData[finalData.columns.values.tolist()[ans-1]]
            print(finalData)

    print("Column removal complete")


    print("\nFinal Attributes:")
    for i, col in enumerate(finalData.columns.values.tolist()):
            print(i+1, ") ", col)

elif option == 2:
    minValue = float(input("Please enter min PC value (the algorithm will remove all attributes with lower values)"))
    for i in range(len(PCvalues)):
        if PCvalues[i] < minValue:
            del finalData[PCnames[i]]
    print("Column removal complete")
    print("\nFinal Attributes:")
    for i, col in enumerate(finalData.columns.values.tolist()[:-1]):
            print(i+1, ") ", col)
            
elif option == 3:
    minValue = float(input("Please enter min Regression value (the algorithm will remove all attributes with lower values)"))
    for i in range(len(REGvalues)):
        if REGvalues[i] < minValue:
            del finalData[REGnames[i]]
    print("Column removal complete")
    print("\nFinal Attributes:")
    for i, col in enumerate(finalData.columns.values.tolist()[:-1]):
            print(i+1, ") ", col)
            
else:
    print("\nFinal Attributes:")
    for i, col in enumerate(finalData.columns.values.tolist()[:-1]):
            print("{:<6}".format(str(i+1) + ") "), col)
